body:
> Team decision: Document that java -cp should be used instead of java -jar ... execute -cp when JVM shutdown hooks are involved.

@marcphilipp I'm writing a build tool, so I don't know if shutdown hooks will be involved or not in the user's test code. Should I then use `java -cp` directly all the time for the user's classes?
If this is viable, then what is the purpose of the separate `-cp` argument of the console launcher?
